RACE.FOOTNOTES: BREAK THE ICE bobbled at the start but broke towards the front, was well placed just off the pace, drafted behind the leader while inside on the turn, was asked in the two path into the stretch, gained to make a bid at the three-sixteenths, took the lead under a right-handed crop coming to the furlong marker then quickly switched to a left-handed crop, shook clear outside the sixteenth-pole then was given one final pop of a left-handed crop and proved best under a strong hand ride to the finish. STEADY PROGRESS was taken in hand early, tracked the pace on the inside of a foe, was asked in the three path while outside on the turn, chased into upper stretch then made a bid near the three-sixteenths, battled outside of two foes under a drive into the final furlong and was outfinished while clear for the place. OLD POINT broke a step slow then was taken in hand with the left rein, settled on the inside, angled out near the three-quarter pole then raced between foes, was urged three wide on the turn, came four wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response while best of the rest. BOLD HONOR moved in while going to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, controlled the action while inside to the two path on the turn, was asked at the quarter-pole then came under a drive, lost the lead to the winner coming to the furlong marker and weakened. DISTURBED settled off the pace, was urged along passing the three-quarter pole, went two to three wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. SHARPOON broke in at the start, settled off the pace, dropped back outside the three-quarter pole, saved ground on the turn and failed to respond. JETER AND JUDGE was off very slow and spotted the front many lengths, settled well back on the outside, moved closer with five furlongs to run, went five then four wide on the turn and had nothing left. FLINTSHIRE'S ROCK broke through the front of the gate prior to the start then was brought back around and reloaded, became nervous in the gate then was off slow and spotted the front a few lengths, angled quickly to the outside then advanced to race up close, came up empty while moving from four to six wide on the turn and retreated then was eased but walked off. MILE FRACTION WAS HAND-TIMED DUE A POSSIBLE TIMING ISSUE AND PROVIDED BY THE NYRA STEWARD

K D KAKES hustled from the gate, vied briefly outside a pair before chasing three wide in aim of the front, advanced into the turn and prompted the pace outside a pair coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch and kept on to the finish. SUSIE'S SAVER broke out at the start bumping JOEY THE FISH, came under coaxing and chased two to three wide, got coaxed along at the three-eighths, angled four wide into upper stretch and offered up a bid but was outkicked. HYPNOCURRENCY chased along the inside under coaxing from the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and made no impact. JOEY THE FISH got bumped at the start by SUSIE'S SAVER, who broke outwards, conceded eight lengths to the front before settling into a sluggish stride and chased three wide down the backstretch detached at the tail of the field and continuing to lose ground, tucked to the two path through the turn, went five to six wide into upper stretch well behind and trailed throughout.

(If the Stewards consider it inadvisable to run this race on the turf course, this race will be run at One Mile on the Main Track.) (Rail at 9 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FATIMA'S BLESSING three wide in pursuit, altered out with a large portion of the field just inside the three-quarter pole when KAZ PALACE began to hurdle light lines across the course, tucked back three wide into the far turn and came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive issuing a challenge through the final furlong taking command a sixteenth out, then dug in to inch away in the late stages and prevail. CONMAN just off the inside early on, altered out to the four path inside the three-quarter pole before tucking back to the two path into the turn, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and spun two to three wide into upper stretch, rallied to take command a furlong out, got collared a sixteenth from home and ran on safe for the place honors. BE OF COURAGE ranged up shortly after the start to briefly duel from the three path with KAZ PALACE to his inside before that rival went rogue and hurdling just inside the six furlong marker and then once more five and a half furlongs out, tucked inside at that juncture now on a lone lead, showed the way through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, continued in the inside route into upper stretch, dug in under threat and was collared a furlong out, kept on to preserve the show honors clear of the rest. NOBLE HUNTSMAN just off the inside in the early stages, altered out to the four path with most of the field to avoid the hurdling KAZ PALACE, tucked three wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled six wide into upper stretch and kept on through to the finish. BARREL OF QUESTS chased two then briefly three wide when altering out a path inside the six furlong marker, tucked back to the two path into the turn and came under coaxing near the quarter pole, swung three wide for home and offered no response. OPEN TIL MIDNIGHT two to three wide in pursuit, tipped out altering four wide briefly midway down the backstretch before tucking three wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch and tired. PLAYINGWITHMATCHES four wide early on, tucked inside to the two path when a larger portion of the field was altering out, tucked to the rail into the turn and came under coaxing three furlongs from home, continued in the inside route into upper stretch and tired. COPPER CHALICE chased three then two wide, came under coaxing inside at the three-eighths, spun three wide for home, made no impact. KAZ PALACE away well and to the front, hopped along seven and a half furlongs out seemingly eyeing the marks of the grass lanes from the mower before settling into brief head to head combat with BE OF COURAGE to the outside, abandoned that duel when hurdling over a line across the track where it dips just inside the six furlong marker, lost two to three lengths of ground to the front forcing the field in behind to alter outwards in caution, hurdled once more the next light line coming out of the dip near five and half furlongs to run, steadily faded into and through the turn before taking the two path into upper stretch and giving way.
